Cityapps Digital Services LLP. Privacy Policy
CityApps Digital Services LLP ("CityApps," "we," or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of our users ("users" or "you"). This Privacy Policy ("Policy") applies to our mobile application ("App") available on the Google Play Store and Apple App Store.
Information Collection and Use:
We collect information you provide directly to us, such as when you create a user account, submit a form, or send us an email.
We also automatically collect certain information about your device and usage of the App, including your device type, operating system version, and App version.
Information Sharing and Disclosure:
We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties.
We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as hosting, data analysis, and customer service.
We may also share your information as required by law or to protect the safety and security of our users and the App.
Data Retention and Security:
We retain your information for as long as your account is active or as needed to provide you services.
We take reasonable measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure.
Your Choices and Rights:
You have the right to request access to and correction of your personal information.
You can also request that we delete your personal information.
You may opt-out of receiving promotional emails from us by following the unsubscribe instructions in such emails.
Changes to this Policy:
We may update this Policy from time to time.
We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Policy on the App or by other means.
Contact Us:
If you have any questions about this Policy or our data practices, please contact us at cityapps.in@gmail.com
By using the App, you consent to our collection, use, and sharing of your information as described in this Policy.
